<enclosure url="http://www.podtrac.com/pts/redirect.mp3/mmpodcast2011.s3.amazonaws.com/mmp002_092611.mp3" length="15297707" type="audio/mpeg" />
			<itunes:keywords>Chickenfoot,YouTube</itunes:keywords>
	<itunes:subtitle>Chickenfoot features Sammy Hagar, Joe Satriani, Michael Anthony, and Chad Smith and they released their third album Chickenfoot III today. To help build up some buzz, they have released a series of videos that give you a double dose of "Behind the musi...</itunes:subtitle>
		<itunes:summary>Chickenfoot features Sammy Hagar, Joe Satriani, Michael Anthony, and Chad Smith and they released their third album Chickenfoot III today. To help build up some buzz, they have released a series of videos that give you a double dose of "Behind the music meets Storytellers." You get to understand what the lyrics are about, as well as gets youy thinking things like, "Am I going to get the hear the weird solo?" You get intimate details of the song and how its about the death of their co-manager.

The bottom line is you can't help but want to hear the song when you get done with the video. They play about 60 seconds of it, and then fade it out - making you want more. This is exactly  what this video is supposed to do and you can do something like this. The videos are well thought out (as each one introduces the next one).

These videos sucked me in? How about you? Do you want to hear more from the new album now?



Video Tips

To make your own video, the AUDIO is the most important thing. Make sure you close enough to be picked up by the microphone, or if you have the technology to pull it off (Like Camtasia Studio) you can record the audio on a portable device and sync the video later.
Easy Video Player
There are tons of tools for video that are free (YouTube for example). This tool is NOT free, but it is focused on getting your more sales. How?

You can embed an email sign up list, RIGHT IN THE VIDEO. You can have the video redirect the viewer to a web page (like your store).

YOU can have "Buy Now" button right in your video.

You get video analytics.

Do split testing with videos.

Secure content from theft (stops people from playing it on their website).

Add overlays that are linkable on your videos.

You can have buy now buttons appear at a certain time.

The thing that sounds annoying about it is it comes with a membership to some marketing website. Granted you can cancel anytime you want, but (for me) if I'm purchasing software I'm not interested in a marketing membership.  The software goes for $127 and if you want the non-branded version it's basically $200.
Chickenfoot Music</itunes:summary>
